docs.abstract: “This is sort of the big kahuna.”
docs.snippet: “This is sort of the big kahuna.”
docs.lead_paragraph: The New York Times sued OpenAI and Microsoft last week for copyright infringement. Kevin Roose and Casey Newton walk through the lawsuit and discuss the stakes for news publishers. Then, they talk about Apple’s “walled garden,” which is facing threats from both regulators and 16-year-olds. Finally, we set our tech resolutions for the new year.

headline.main: The Times Sues OpenAI, a Debate Over iMessage and Our New Year’s Tech Resolutions

byline.original: By Kevin Roose, Casey Newton, Davis Land, Rachel Cohn, Kate LoPresti, Jen Poyant, Daniel Ramirez, Dan Powell, Marion Lozano, Rowan Niemisto and Pat McCusker

docs.abstract: Amazon, Google, Microsoft and other tech companies have been on a layoff spree this month, with the latest cuts differing from last year’s mass reductions.
docs.snippet: Amazon, Google, Microsoft and other tech companies have been on a layoff spree this month, with the latest cuts differing from last year’s mass reductions.
docs.lead_paragraph: Last year, Mark Zuckerberg declared 2023 to be a “year of efficiency.” His company, Meta, soon laid off a third of its employees. Amazon, Google and Microsoft also cut tens of thousands of workers.

headline.main: Focused Cuts and Fewer Layers: Tech Layoffs Enter a New Phase
